            {
                "name": "Decade",
                "url": "/topics/decade"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734615",
        "quote": "In the past, a writer had to go outside and get to know others before learning about their work, but the Internet has made humanity more accessible for misanthropes like me. I read blogs, tweets, Facebook posts and Reddit threads where people detail their jobs.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Victor LaValle",
            "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734615"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Accessible",
                "url": "/topics/accessible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Blogs",
                "url": "/topics/blogs"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734616",
        "quote": "Social media give me the privilege of learning about more people than I could meet in my whole life. Taken together, the Internet reads like the grandest character-driven novel humanity has ever known. Not much plot, though.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Victor LaValle",
            "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734616"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Learning",
                "url": "/topics/learning"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Whole",
                "url": "/topics/whole"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734617",
        "quote": "One of the most widely read novels by a black American is Ralph Ellison's 'Invisible Man.' It is his masterwork - it won the National Book Award in 1953 and catapulted my man to the highest levels of literary esteem.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Victor LaValle",
            "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734617"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Book",
                "url": "/topics/book"
            },
            {
                "name": "Invisible",
                "url": "/topics/invisible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Literary",
                "url": "/topics/literary"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734618",
        "quote": "The project of Ralph Ellison's 'Invisible Man' is exactly that: to assert the beautiful, bountiful, chaotic complexity of one black American male. And, by extension, all black American males.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Victor LaValle",
            "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734618"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Complexity",
                "url": "/topics/complexity"
            },
            {
                "name": "Extension",
                "url": "/topics/extension"
            },
            {
                "name": "Ralph",
                "url": "/topics/ralph"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734619",
        "quote": "I didn't grow up in a small New England town like the one in 'The Sundial.' I was raised in an apartment building in Queens, not in a sprawling, slightly sinister mansion like the one where the Halloran family resides.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Victor LaValle",
            "url": "/quotes/victor_lavalle_734619"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
